                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure will persist across the coastal waters. The high pressure centre associated with the ridge will become established in the Tasman Sea over the weekend. A trough moves over the south early next week with a cold front clipping the southeast mid week. A new ridge develops south of the Bight early to mid next week.</text>
                <text type="preamble">Wind and wave forecasts are averages. Wind gusts can be 40 per cent stronger than the forecast, and stronger still in squalls and thunderstorms. Maximum waves can be twice the forecast height.</text>
